  421. Stiff - but do loosen up if bent and rolled a little in the fingers. Well worth the money since overall it saves me so much on lashes - most other lashes cost well over the price I paid for these but since I get (20) pairs for this price I'd be crazy to pass up this deal. For first timers using fake eyelashes it may be a little nerve racking but here is how I apply..<br /><br />First I hold a fake eyelash up to my eye and try and size it. I cut off the extra amount if they are larger than my eyes (which they are). Then I roll them in my fingers a bit to loosen the lashes up so they aren't so stiff feeling / looking. Once I feel like they are flexible enough I apply eyelash glue to them (do not use real glue, and also the eyelash glue does not come in the set - so that will need to be purchased separate). I let the glue sit on the lash for about a minute before trying to apply them to my lashes..this gives the glue time to set. (use tweezers to apply if fingers seem to get in your way). Curling these with a lash curler and applying mascara makes them look more realistic. Good luck!

  1417. I read some of the reviews before I bought them and even though some were bad, I couldn't resist the temptation for cheap lashes. These lashes are so soft. I believe they are hand-made. 10 of the lashes are super thick and the other 10 are thin but longer. These lashes don't come with glue (but a lot of lashes don't). I had some handy anyway. I had to cut off the ends of the lashes (the bits keeping them in the box) but otherwise they're ready to go. I had to do a couple of coats of glue because the part that you glue basically fabric. Nothing glue couldn't handle though. At first they were hard to put on because they are not pre-curved to fit your eyelid. That also is fixed with the extra glue coats. I had to apply eyeliner around them to make them look at least a little more natural. The thin lashes could look natural but the thick lashes are total desu manga lashes. For me, I found that as a plus. I love them. The thick lashes can get heavy (so if you're looking for desu manga &#34;come hither&#34; bedroom eyes they are perfect). I do like the thin lashes better. Further down in the review, I'll be posting pictures and I used the thin lashes on the bottom lash line just to see how the two different lashes would fit together. If you're looking for a natural look but lengthy lashes, this is a pretty good buy just for the ten thin lashes.
